60747: meta-amd: Remove skeleton_workbook | https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/openbmc/+/60747
Please add a common include for meta-amd that does this so it isn't forgotten on other machines.

60746: meta-amd: Create common machine configuration file | https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/openbmc/+/60746
The ALLOW_EMPTY doesn't jive with having a do_install.  Is everything going into the -dev package?  Should this be a -native recipe?

I haven't looked much at how it really works, but this configuration is present in all other IPMI YAML recipes, for example:
https://github.com/openbmc/openbmc/blob/master/meta-yadro/meta-nicole/recipes-phosphor/configuration/nicole-yaml-config.bb
https://github.com/openbmc/openbmc/blob/master/meta-facebook/meta-bletchley/recipes-phosphor/configuration/bletchley-yaml-config.bb
https://github.com/openbmc/openbmc/blob/master/meta-ingrasys/meta-zaius/recipes-phosphor/configuration/zaius-yaml-config.bb
https://github.com/openbmc/openbmc/blob/master/meta-inspur/meta-fp5280g2/recipes-phosphor/configuration/fp5280g2-yaml-config.bb
https://github.com/openbmc/openbmc/blob/master/meta-ampere/meta-jade/recipes-phosphor/configuration/mtjade-yaml-config.bb
https://github.com/openbmc/openbmc/blob/master/meta-ibm/recipes-phosphor/configuration/acx22-yaml-config.bb
https://github.com/openbmc/openbmc/blob/master/meta-quanta/meta-gbs/recipes-phosphor/configuration/gbs-yaml-config.bb
etc.
We should not be adding new EM json files in this repo.  Please contribute upstream.

Unfortunately the FRU EEPROM is empty on my board and the format is not documented by AMD, so I can't write anything besides the `"Probe": "TRUE"` in the JSON file, which is obviously can't be submitted upstream.
Also I'm afrad that the actual AMD FRU format would look like the one on the EthanolX board. It is a custom format with a FRU content prepended with a MAC address. And EM can't yet parse such FRUs.
This is why I took the approach that is used on the EthanolX board:
https://github.com/openbmc/openbmc/blob/332ee51c0d8de048704c31cacc78c8d3aaf77b54/meta-amd/meta-ethanolx/recipes-phosphor/configuration/entity-manager/ethanolx-baseboard.json#L1470
Why are there so many "RESERVED" instances?  Can't you just drop the reserved ones?

I'm not sure, can I?

This file is based on the primary JSON file from the openbmc repo:
https://github.com/openbmc/openbmc/blob/master/meta-phosphor/recipes-phosphor/ipmi/phosphor-ipmi-config/channel_config.json

It already has 15 channels with 10 marked as `RESERVED`. Why does it has all these channels then?

The DaytonaX configuration is based on that file, but just disables 3 more channels:
```
 0 IPMB (ipmb)
 2 eth1 (lan-802.3)
14 SELF (ipmb)
```

I was looking into this myself lately and the RESERVED ones are due to some buggy code that I just fixed in phosphor-ipmi that would spam the log if you didn't enumerate all 16 possible channels.  Whoever wrote that config decided it was better to write worthless JSON than fix the underlying problem.

Anyhow since this is mimicking what is already in place, I won't hold anything up for it.
As a warning it is not preferred to use YAML for configuring phosphor-led-manager anymore.

I've investigated how to write a required JSON file, and I can submit a patchset that would add it to the `phosphor-led-manager` via the .bbappend file, i.e.:
```
meta-amd/meta-ethanolx/recipes-phosphor/leds/phosphor-led-manager_%.bbappend

meta-amd/meta-ethanolx/recipes-phosphor/leds/phosphor-led-manager/led-group-config.json
```
But as I understand, you want this file `led-group-config.json` to be submitted directly to the `phosphor-led-manager` repo. In this case I'm not sure how the board can select appropriate JSON file. I'm not sure if this functionality is supported now.

You would need to add a "Compatible" interface exposed by your entity-manager config, which corresponds to the JSON file you're adding the the phosphor-led-manager.  That "Compatible" interface is what the IBM examples are exposing.

The `phosphor-led-manager` uses hardcoded interface `IBMCompatibleSystem`
https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-led-manager/blob/3e073ba61793e3f5889a0c4ae81e84bf489d7738/manager/json-config.hpp#L20

This is how it is used in the EM:
https://github.com/openbmc/entity-manager/blob/dcf24b0d615848961daff167c7e45dfa4c6b4c51/schemas/ibm.json#L50
https://github.com/openbmc/entity-manager/blob/51cff4b46543f74ffda77443f04a3ce0f16b4f27/configurations/everest.json#L8

I think I shouldn't touch the `IBMCompatibleSystem` property in my EM config.
So it looks like `phosphor-led-manager` and `EM` will need some modifications before they can be used like you suggest.

Should I push a patch with a `*.bbappend` solution for now, or should I just leave YAML config?

> I think I shouldn't touch the IBMCompatibleSystem property in my EM config.

I didn't realize that still wasn't fixed.  Right there is a real Compatible interface now instead of this non-documented IBM one.  That was suppose to be transitioned over.
Seems to follow existing conventions fine enough.  Supreeth has had plenty of time to weigh in and doesn't usually pay much attention, so I'm going to +2 this.
